^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Good try. I don't think the hand can be made. However, let's discuss the bidding. The bids through 2H are fine. 3D by Elizabeth shows a fairly strong hand, it is sort of a reverse, in the sense that she is bidding past her suit at the 2 level. So she should either have a lot of points or distribution. She does have distribution. So, 3D is risky but okay. However, once I bid 3N she should pass. She does not want to use her AK of hearts to ruff out clubs. As you already know, I define a reverse as voluntarily bidding past your suit at the 2 level. since 2S was available 3D is a reverse. |
PG| ***** 18 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|If I have QJ fifth of hearts she can count six tricks for sure, assuming I have a club stopper and I have the Ace of diamonds, 3N must have plays. And it turns out 3N does make if I duck a diamond early. I will four diamonds, three hearts, a spade, and a club. Against perfect defense it does not make, but if they play perfect defense, then I am allowed to drop the doubleton @DQ and make the hand, lol. So, in real life it will probably make. |
