PG| ***** 58 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|One other point regarding the opening lead. Elizabeth has a raft of poor choices. A singleton trump is not a good lead in general, unless a trump lead is clear cut. Certainly on this auction a trump lead is not clear cut. Singleton trumps often give away tricks. if Barbara had another honor besides the A, it would have given away a trick. So, a heart is out. In NT, a spade lead would be fine. But, leading away from honors in a suit contract is very aggressive particularly when there is a lot of strength concentrated on your right. |
PG| ***** 59 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Certainly, if East has a spade card, a spade lead could work out great. So, there was some merit to the spade lead but I would give it a lower priority. A club lead is even lower priority than a spade lead because the clubs are not as good, and has the same problem of leading away from an honor and doubletons are not strong leads either. I would have chosen a diamond, as the least likely to give something away, but a spade has some merit as I said before.|
