NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Now, let us look at Barbara's declarer points and Elizabeth's dummy points, once Barbara bids 1S. Once East bids 1S, Elizabeth counts as follows: 14 HCP, one quality suit for 15 Starting Points, and one point for the doubleton for 16 Dummy Points total in spades. Not quite strong enough to bid 3S, which, in Marty Bergen's methods, shows 17-19. Remember, Bergen has lots of addons, so he jumps with more Bergen points. So, Elizabeth has a maximum 2S bid as it turns out. Now, let's look at Barbara's hand. She has 10 HCP + one length point = 11 Starting Points. Once Elizabeth raises spades, she can add 2 points for the singleton, and 1 point for the 4-card side suit, which gives her a total of 14. Therefore using Bergen methods, she has enough to bid 4S. However, as I said, those unfamiliar with Bergen, many would bid 3S.|
